  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life Skills and Peer Education for 14,000 students</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Windhoek&apos;s most disadvantaged areas the use of alcohol and drugs is on the rise and drug-related crime is wide-spread. Blue Cross Namibia has developed a project in 15 Windhoek high schools to prevent substance abuse by empowering students through peer-educators to lead healthy lives. Children and youth are taught &quot;life skills,&quot; participate in after-school activity clubs like chess or soccer and hold rallies/awareness events in the communities to fight addiction and promote a drug-free life.</narrative>
  </description>
